      <persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Namık</forename><surname>Görgüç</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.7d5d8ec5">Görgüç, Namık</ref></persName><persName role="Press Photographer"><forename>Selahattin </forename><surname>Giz</surname><ref type="context" target="info:fedora/context:siba.pn.dce0efc3">Giz, Selahattin </ref></persName></ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">A group of men is herding a large flock of sheep across the yard of an industrial building. A large group of men dressed mostly in coats and hats or flat caps is assembled at the back of the yard.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The picture was probably taken in the context of an article reporting on the slaughterhouse in Sütlüce on the Golden Horn, maybe on the occasion of the preparations for <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=K16">Kurban</ref> <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B2">bayram</ref>ı. Preparations for this religious holiday and the start of festivities were reported in short articles and pictures that sometimes reappeared a year or two later on the same or similar occasions.</ab>
